gust 2008|accessdate=14 May 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180514213546/https://www.iol.co.za/capeargus/sport/big-money-lure-for-psls-golden-boot-592894|archive-date=2018-05-14|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Premier Soccer League 2008-09|2008\u201309]]\n!scope=\"row\"|{{sortname|Richard|Henyekane}}\n|{{flag|South Africa}}\n|[[Lamontville Golden Arrows F.C.|Golden Arrows]]\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|19\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.sport24.co.za/Soccer/PSL/Teko-does-it-again-20090525|title=Teko does it again|publisher=Sport 24|date=25 May 2009|accessdate=14 May 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180514214051/https://www.sport24.co.za/Soccer/PSL/Teko-does-it-again-20090525|archive-date=2018-05-14|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Premier Soccer League 2009-10|2009\u201310]]\n!scope=\"row\"|{{sortname|Katlego|Mphela}}\n|{{flag|South Africa}}\n|[[Mamelodi Sundowns F.C.|Mamelodi Sundowns]]\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|17\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|<ref name=hist/>\n|-\n|[[Premier Soccer League 2010-11|2010\u201311]]\n!scope=\"row\"|{{sortname|Knowledge|Musona}}\n|{{flag|Zimbabwe}}\n|[[Kaizer Chiefs F.C.|Kaizer Chiefs]]\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|17\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|<ref name=hist/>\n|-\n|[[Premier Soccer League 2011-12|2011\u201312]]\n!scope=\"row\"|{{sortname|Siyabonga|Nomvethe}}\n|{{flag|South Africa}}\n|[[Moroka Swallows]]\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|20\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.kickoff.com/news/28631/moroka-swallows-striker-siyabonga-nomvete-was-the-big-winner-at-psl-awards|title=Moroka Swallows striker Siyabonga Nomvethe was the big winner at PSL Awards|publisher=Kick Off|date=28 May 2012|accessdate=14 May 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180514213801/http://www.kickoff.com/news/28631/moroka-swallows-striker-siyabonga-nomvete-was-the-big-winner-at-psl-awards|archive-date=2018-05-14|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Premier Soccer League 2012-13|2012\u201313]]\n!scope=\"row\"|{{sortname|Katlego|Mashego}}\n|{{flag|South Africa}}\n|[[Moroka Swallows]]\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|13\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.kickoff.com/news/34494/moroka-swallows-striker-katlego-mashego-wins-golden-boot|title=Moroka Swallows striker Katlego Mashego wins Golden Boot|publisher=Kick Off|date=18 May 2013|accessdate=14 May 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180514213820/http://www.kickoff.com/news/34494/moroka-swallows-striker-katlego-mashego-wins-golden-boot|archive-date=2018-05-14|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Premier Soccer League 2013-14|2013\u201314]]\n!scope=\"row\"|{{sortname|Bernard|Parker}}\n|{{flag|South Africa}}\n|[[Kaizer Chiefs F.C.|Kaizer Chiefs]]\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|10\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.kickoff.com/news/44370/psl-golden-boot-or-bronze-boot|title=PSL Golden Boot, or bronze boot?|publisher=Kick Off|date=12 May 2014|accessdate=14 May 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180905175918/http://www.kickoff.com/news/44370/psl-golden-boot-or-bronze-boot|archive-date=2018-09-05|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[2014-15 Premier Soccer League |2014\u201315]]\n!scope=\"row\"|{{sortname|Moeketsi|Sekola}}\n|{{flag|South Africa}}\n|[[Free State Stars F.C.|Free State Stars]]\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|14\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.kickoff.com/news/55253/moeketsi-sekola-wins-lesley-manyathela-golden-boot-award|title=Moeketsi Sekola wins Lesley Manyathela Golden Boot award|publisher=Kick Off|date=9 May 2015|accessdate=14 May 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180514213848/http://www.kickoff.com/news/55253/moeketsi-sekola-wins-lesley-manyathela-golden-boot-award|archive-date=2018-05-14|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[2015-16 Premier Soccer League|2015\u201316]]\n!scope=\"row\"|{{sortname|Collins|Mbesuma}} (2)\n|{{flag|Zambia}}\n|[[Mpumalanga Black Aces F.C.|Mpumalanga Black Aces]]\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|14\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.soccerladuma.co.za/news/articles/categories/south-africa/collins-mbesuma-wins-the-absa-premiership-golden-boot/231106|title=Collins Mbesuma Wins The Absa Premiership Golden Boot|publisher=Soccer Laduma|date=23 May 2016|accessdate=14 May 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180514213711/https://www.soccerladuma.co.za/news/articles/categories/south-africa/collins-mbesuma-wins-the-absa-premiership-golden-boot/231106|archive-date=2018-05-14|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Premier Soccer League 2016-17|2016\u201317]]\n!scope=\"row\"|{{sortname|Lebogang|Manyama}}\n|{{flag|South Africa}}\n|[[Cape Town City F.C. (2016)|Cape Town City]]\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|13\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.kickoff.com/news/75662/cape-town-citys-lebogang-manyama-wins-psls-golden-boot|title=Cape Town City's Lebogang Manyama wins PSL's Golden Boot|publisher=Kick Off|date=27 May 2017|accessdate=14 May 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180514213456/http://www.kickoff.com/news/75662/cape-town-citys-lebogang-manyama-wins-psls-golden-boot|archive-date=2018-05-14|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"#B0C4DE\"|[[2017\u201318 South African Premier Division|2017\u201318]]{{sup|{{dagger}}}}\n!scope=\"row\"|{{sortname|Rodney|Ramagalela}}\n|{{flag|South Africa}}\n|[[Polokwane City F.C.|Polokwane City]]\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|11\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|<ref name=share>{{cite news|url=https://m.sport24.co.za/Soccer/PSL/tau-kekana-nominated-for-psl-footballer-of-the-season-20180521|title=Sundowns dominate PSL Award nominations|publisher=News 24|date=21 May 2018|accessdate=23 May 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180523173134/https://m.sport24.co.za/Soccer/PSL/tau-kekana-nominated-for-psl-footballer-of-the-season-20180521|archive-date=2018-05-23|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"#B0C4DE\"|[[2017\u201318 South African Premier Division|2017\u201318]]{{sup|{{dagger}}}}\n!scope=\"row\"|{{sortname|Percy|Tau}}\n|{{flag|South Africa}}\n|scope=\"row\" style=\"background:#FFE6BD\"|[[Mamelodi Sundowns F.C.|Mamelodi Sundowns]]{{sup|{{double-dagger}}}}\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|11\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|<ref name=share/>\n|-\n|[[2018\u201319 South African Premier Division|2018\u201319]]\n!scope=\"row\"|{{sortname|Mwape|Musonda}}\n|{{flag|Zambia}}\n|[[Black Leopards F.C.|Black Leopards]]\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|16\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thesouthafrican.com/psl-top-goal-scorers-for-2018-19-season/|title=PSL: Top goal scorers for 2018/19 season|publisher=The South African|last=Breakfast|first=Siviwe|date=11 May 2019|accessdate=11 May 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Awards won by nationality==\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n!scope=\"col\"|Country\n!scope=\"col\"|Total\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{flagcountry|South Africa}}\n|align=\"center\"|{{nts|14}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{flagcountry|Zambia}}\n|align=\"center\"|{{nts|6}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{flagcountry|Zimbabwe}}\n|align=\"center\"|{{nts|3}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{flagcountry|Senegal}}\n|align=\"center\"|{{nts|1}}\n|}\n\n==Awards by club==\n\n[[File:Mame Niang.jpg|thumb|[[Mame Niang]] (pictured here during his time with Norwegian side [[Viking FK|Viking]]) is one of four [[Moroka Swallows F.C.|Moroka Swallows]] players to have won the Golden Boot award.]]\n\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n!scope=\"col\"|Club\n!scope=\"col\"|Total\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |[[Moroka Swallows F.C.|Moroka Swallows]]\n| align=\"center\" |{{nts|4}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[Kaizer Chiefs F.C.|Kaizer Chiefs]]\n|align=\"center\"|{{nts|4}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[Manning Rangers F.C.|Manning Rangers]]\n|align=\"center\"|{{nts|3}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[Mamelodi Sundowns F.C.|Mamelodi Sundowns]]\n|align=\"center\"|{{nts|2}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[Orlando Pirates]]\n|align=\"center\"|{{nts|2}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[Bush Bucks F.C.|Bush Bucks]]\n|align=\"center\"|{{nts|1}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[Cape Town City F.C. (2016)|Cape Town City]]\n|align=\"center\"|{{nts|1}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[Free State Stars F.C.|Free State Stars]]\n|align=\"center\"|{{nts|1}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[Lamontville Golden Arrows F.C.|Golden Arrows]]\n|align=\"center\"|{{nts|1}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[Jomo Cosmos F.C.|Jomo Cosmos]]\n|align=\"center\"|{{nts|1}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[Mpumalanga Black Aces F.C.|Mpumalanga Black Aces]]\n|align=\"center\"|{{nts|1}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[Polokwane City F.C.|Polokwane City]]\n|align=\"center\"|{{nts|1}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[AmaZulu F.C.|Zulu Royals]]\n|align=\"center\"|{{nts|1}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[Black Leopards F.C.|Black Leopards]]\n|align=\"center\"|{{nts|1}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Premier Soccer League awards}}\n{{Portal bar|Association football|Football in Africa}}\n\n{{featured list}}\n[[Category:Premier Soccer League]]\n[[Category:African football trophies and awards]]\n[[Category:Soccer in South Africa]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox award\n| name = Lesley Manyathela Golden Boot\n| subheader = <!-- or | current_awards = -->\n| image = \n| image_size = \n| alt = \n| caption = \n| description = The leading goalscorer in a given Premier Division season.\n| sponsor = \n| country = South Africa\n| presenter = [[Premier Soccer League]]\n| former name = \n| year = 1997\n| year2 = 2019\n| holder = [[Mwape Musonda]] <!-- or | winner = or | winners = -->\n| most_wins = [[Collins Mbesuma]] (2)\n}}\n\n'''The Lesley Manyathela Golden Boot''' is an annual [[association football]] award presented by the [[Premier Soccer League]] to the leading goalscorer in the [[South African Premier Division]].<ref>{{cite web|title=NSL Constitution|url=http://images.supersport.com/NSL%20Constitution%20as%20amended%2013%20November%202010.pdf|publisher=Premier Soccer League|format=pdf|accessdate=13 December 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304041154/http://images.supersport.com/NSL%20Constitution%20as%20amended%2013%20November%202010.pdf|archive-date=4 March 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> The award, colloquially known as the golden boot or PSL Golden Boot, has been presented since the inception of the post-[[apartheid]] format of the league in 1996. It was named in 2003 in honour of [[Lesley Manyathela]], a [[South Africa national football team|South African international]] footballer and former recipient of the award who died in a motor vehicle collision in August of that year.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/Safa-retires-Lesleys-jersey-20030814|title=Safa retires Lesley's jersey|publisher=News 24|date=15 August 2003|accessdate=17 May 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180517153450/https://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/Safa-retires-Lesleys-jersey-20030814|archive-date=2018-05-17|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[Wilfred Mugeyi]] was the first recipient of the award after he scored 22 goals for [[Bush Bucks F.C.|Bush Bucks]] in the [[1996\u201397 Premier Soccer League|inaugural Premier Division season]].<ref name=hist>{{cite news|url=http://vodacomsoccer.co.za/news/general/168/throwback-thursday:-golden-boot-winners-of-yesteryear|title=Throwback Thursday: Golden Boot winners of yesteryear|publisher=Vodacom Soccer|accessdate=6 September 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180906163239/http://vodacomsoccer.co.za/news/general/168/throwback-thursday:-golden-boot-winners-of-yesteryear|archive-date=2018-09-06|url-status=live}}</ref> He is one of only four players to have scored 20 or more goals in a season alongside [[Pollen Ndlanya]], [[Collins Mbesuma]] and [[Siyabonga Nomvethe]].<ref name=hist/> Mbesuma holds the record for the most goals scored in a single season following his return of 25 goals for [[Kaizer Chiefs]] in the [[Premier Soccer League 2004-05|2004\u201305 season]].<ref name=CM>{{cite news|url=https://www.soccerladuma.co.za/news/get-published-show/who-will-break-mbesumas-record-25-goals/229363|title=Can Anyone Break Mbesuma's Record?|publisher=Soccer Laduma|date=19 April 2016|accessdate=14 May 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180515043550/https://www.soccerladuma.co.za/news/get-published-show/who-will-break-mbesumas-record-25-goals/229363|archive-date=2018-05-15|url-status=dead}}</ref> He is also the only player to have won the award more than once, having claimed the trophy for a second time during his spell with [[Mpumalanga Black Aces F.C.|Mpumalanga Black Aces]] in 2016.<ref name=CM/> \n\n[[Bernard Parker]] holds the record for the fewest goals needed to win the award, with his return of 10 goals for Kaizer Chiefs in the [[Premier Soccer League 2013-14|2013\u201314 season]] earning him the accolade.<ref name=TGS>{{cite news|url=https://www.iol.co.za/sport/soccer/psl/sundowns-tau-polokwanes-ramagalela-in-two-way-race-for-golden-boot-14718532|title=Sundowns' Tau, Polokwane's Ramagalela in two-way race for Golden Boot|publisher=Independent Online|date=30 April 2018|accessdate=5 September 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180905175929/https://www.iol.co.za/sport/soccer/psl/sundowns-tau-polokwanes-ramagalela-in-two-way-race-for-golden-boot-14718532|archive-date=2018-09-05|url-status=live}}</ref> The award has only been shared once in the Premier Division's history, an occurrence which took place after the [[2017\u201318 South African Premier Division|2017\u201318 season]] after [[Rodney Ramagalela]] of [[Polokwane City F.C.|Polokwane City]] and [[Percy Tau]] of [[Mamelodi Sundowns F.C.|Mamelodi Sundowns]] both ended the campaign on 11 goals.<ref name=TGS/> Players from [[Moroka Swallows F.C.|Moroka Swallows]] and Kaizer Chiefs have won the award the most times, with each club having four unique winners.<ref name=hist/> The award has been won on fourteen occasions by South African nationals, the most by any nation.\n\n==Winners==\n[[File:Bernard Parker FC Twente.jpg|thumb|right|[[Bernard Parker]] (pictured here during his time with Dutch side [[FC Twente|Twente]]) holds the record for the fewest goals needed to win the award. His tally of 10 goals for [[Kaizer Chiefs]] earned him the Golden Boot in 2014.|alt=Bernard Parker holds the record for the lowest number of goals needed to win the award.]]\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|+Key\n!scope=\"row\"|'''Player {{small|(X)}}\n|Name of the player and number of times they had won the award at that point (if more than one)\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center; background:#B0C4DE\"|{{dagger}}\n|Indicates multiple award winners in the same season\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center; background:#FFE6BD\"|{{double-dagger}}\n|Denotes the club were [[South African Premier Division]] champions in the same season\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|+Lesley Manyathela Golden Boot winners\n!scope=\"col\"|Season\n!scope=\"col\"|Player\n!scope=\"col\"|Nationality\n!scope=\"col\"|Club\n!scope=\"col\"|Goals\n!scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"|{{abbr|Ref|Reference}}\n|-\n|[[Premier Soccer League 1996-97|1996\u201397]]\n!scope=\"row\"|{{sortname|Wilfred|Mugeyi}}\n|{{flag|Zimbabwe}}\n|[[Bush Bucks F.C. (1957)|Bush Bucks]]\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|22\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|<ref name=hist/>\n|-\n|[[Premier Soccer League 1997-98|1997\u201398]]\n!scope=\"row\"|{{sortname|Keryn|Jordan}}\n|{{flag|South Africa}}\n|[[Manning Rangers]]\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|11\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|<ref name=hist/>\n|-\n|[[Premier Soccer League 1998-99|1998\u201399]]\n!scope=\"row\"|{{sortname|Pollen|Ndlanya}}\n|{{flag|South Africa}}\n|[[Kaizer Chiefs F.C.|Kaizer Chiefs]]\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|21\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|<ref name=hist/>\n|-\n|[[Premier Soccer League 1999-00|1999\u201300]]\n!scope=\"row\"|{{sortname|Dennis|Lota}}\n|{{flag|Zambia}}\n|[[Orlando Pirates]]\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|18\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|<ref